The paper deals with a communication system involving relays and joint processing, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of LDPC codes and Belief Propagation decoding also suggests a focus on coding theory (cs.IT) and error correction (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the design of a low-complexity architecture, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and computer architecture (cs.CC).
